title: 'Very sharp knife with a sturdy handle'
body: The first thing to notice about the knife after I took it out was how sharp the serrated edge is. You will definitely need to be careful while using it, because their is a risk of getting your fingers cut. It cuts through most vegetables and fruits that I have tried this far by without any effort.  The handle also looks sturdy and doesn't buckle at all even when a little pressure is applied. The knife edge will last i am certain, whether the handle is durable, will have to wait and see. Looks good as well. Definitely worth the price.

title: 'Been using this for a year now'
body: 'I have been using this product for a year now and my maid was so impressed with it she wanted me to order one for her. I ordered one for her. This is not exactly the same brand as I am using but looks like same product with different label. Will update the review soon.'

title: 'The Tomato knife'
body: 'MY DIL bought me this knife on her last visit to India. I cant tell you how perfect it is to pare any kind of fruit. Its great ofcourse to chop tomatoes but it also does a lot of other stuff.  Buy one or GIFT it if you are a cook. Makes life so much simpler and easy.  Marianne'
